{"priority": "trivial", "kind": "enhancement", "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/handsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/handsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{9c7d89af-6eb6-40b1-9f69-da1ae9d129ce}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "handsim", "full_name": "osrf/handsim", "uuid": "{9c7d89af-6eb6-40b1-9f69-da1ae9d129ce}"}, "links": {"attachments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/handsim/issues/83/attachments_page=1.json"}, "self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/handsim/issues/83.json"}, "watch": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/handsim/issues/83/watch"}, "comments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/handsim/issues/83/comments_page=1.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/handsim/issues/83/add-instructions-to-install-libusb-when"}, "vote": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/handsim/issues/83/vote"}}, "reporter": {"display_name": "Louise Poubel", "uuid": "{5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8/7d903d90-c5ea-4182-b7ef-0d467e9e1c74/128"}}, "nickname": "chapulina", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8"}, "title": "Add instructions to install libusb when compiling from source", "component": null, "votes": 0, "watches": 3, "content": {"raw": "After building `gazebo`, `ing-transport` and `haptix-comm`, I got this error when building `handsim`:\r\n\r\n~~~\r\n/home/louise/code/handsim/src/polhemus_driver.c:22:31: fatal error: libusb-1.0/libusb.h: No such file or directory\r\n #include <libusb-1.0/libusb.h>\r\n~~~\r\n\r\nWhich I solved by doing\r\n\r\n~~~\r\nsudo apt-get install libusb-1.0-0-dev\r\n~~~\r\n\r\nThis could be added to the README, or maybe if libusb can't be found, polhemus (and hydra?) stuff doesn't get compiled and you just get a warning...?", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>After building <code>gazebo</code>, <code>ing-transport</code> and <code>haptix-comm</code>, I got this error when building <code>handsim</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">home</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">louise</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">code</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">handsim</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">src</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">polhemus_driver</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nl\">c</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">22</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">31</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">fatal</span> <span class=\"nl\">error</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">libusb</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mf\">1.0</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">libusb</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nl\">h</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">No</span> <span class=\"n\">such</span> <span class=\"n\">file</span> <span class=\"n\">or</span> <span class=\"n\">directory</span>\n <span class=\"cp\">#include</span> <span class=\"cpf\">&lt;libusb-1.0/libusb.h&gt;</span><span class=\"cp\"></span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>Which I solved by doing</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span>sudo apt-get install libusb-1.0-0-dev\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>This could be added to the README, or maybe if libusb can't be found, polhemus (and hydra?) stuff doesn't get compiled and you just get a warning...?</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": {"display_name": "Louise Poubel", "uuid": "{5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B5cf